<body lang="en-IN" text="#111827" link="#000080" vlink="#800000" dir="ltr"><h1 class="western">
AI Usage Report</h1>
<p class="meta"><strong>Plugin:</strong> WS Team Showcase Widget
-Avijit<br/>
<strong>Plugin Slug:</strong>
ws-team-showcase-widget-avijit<br/>
<strong>Author:</strong> Avijit
Dhar<br/>
<strong>AI Tool Used:</strong> Codex<br/>
<strong>Report
Purpose:</strong> Compact stepwise summary of AI-assisted planning,
implementation, debugging, and refinement for the Elementor team
showcase plugin.</p>
<h2 class="western">1. Objective</h2>
<p>The objective was to create and update a custom WordPress
Elementor widget named <strong>WS Team Showcase</strong>. The widget
needed dynamic team member management, responsive cards, AJAX
filtering, search, popup details, load-more pagination, ACF repeater
integration, style controls, and backend-managed bonus features.</p>
<h2 class="western">2. Required Feature Coverage</h2>
<table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2">
	<tr>
		<th style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Feature</p>
		</th>
		<th style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Implementation Summary</p>
		</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Elementor Widget</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Created with OOP PHP
			using Elementor <code>Widget_Base</code>.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Manual Repeater</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added repeater fields for
			name, designation, department, bio, image, social links,
			experience, and CTA button data.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>ACF Integration</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added <code>Team
			Showcases</code> custom post type and local ACF repeater field
			group for reusable team data.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Data Source Switch</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added backend choice
			between <code>Manual Repeater</code> and <code>ACF Repeater</code>.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Responsive Grid</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added grid controls for
			desktop, tablet, and mobile cards per row under <code>Grid
			Settings</code>.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>AJAX Filtering</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added nonce-protected
			AJAX filtering by department and search query.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Search Filter</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added search input with
			backend toggle, icon picker, and style controls.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Popup Modal</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Popup opens by clicking
			team member image or title. The separate View Details button was
			removed.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Load More AJAX</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Automatically appears
			when more than 8 members exist. AJAX appends the next page of
			members.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Lazy Loading</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Images use lazy loading
			with backend toggle.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Skeleton Loader</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Skeleton loader added for
			AJAX loading and made backend-manageable.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>GSAP Animation</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added optional GSAP
			entrance animation controlled from the backend.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Dark Mode</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added backend dark mode
			toggle and CSS overrides for cards, text, filters, and search
			input.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Button Controls</p>
		</td>
		<td style="border: none; padding: 0cm"><p>Added Elementor-like
			member button fields: type, text, link, icon, icon position, icon
			spacing, and button ID.</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<h2 class="western">3. Stepwise AI-Assisted Build Summary</h2>
<h3 class="western">Step 1: Initial Plugin Review</h3>
<p>The AI inspected the existing plugin folder and identified the
main files: plugin bootstrap, Elementor widget class, AJAX handler,
CSS, JS, and README. It confirmed the plugin already had a manual
repeater, frontend card rendering, AJAX filtering, popup, and
load-more basics.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 2: Custom Post Type and ACF Repeater</h3>
<p>The AI added a new PHP class for post type and ACF registration. A
<code>Team Showcases</code> custom post type was created, and an ACF
local field group was registered with a main <code>Team Members</code>
repeater and nested social links repeater.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 3: Elementor Data Source Switch</h3>
<p>The widget was updated with a backend <code>Data Source</code>
control. Admins can now choose between manual Elementor repeater data
and an ACF-backed Team Showcase post.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 4: ACF Member Normalization</h3>
<p>The AI implemented helper methods to normalize ACF fields into the
same data structure used by the manual repeater. This allowed both
data sources to share the same rendering, filtering, popup, and
load-more logic.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 5: Runtime Fatal Error Fix</h3>
<p>A fatal error occurred because the WordPress admin helper <code>hidden()</code>
was used in an Elementor frontend render context. The AI replaced it
with direct HTML attribute output.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 6: Skeleton Loader Display Fix</h3>
<p>The skeleton loader appeared at the bottom even when hidden
because CSS <code>display: grid</code> overrode the browser hidden
behavior. The AI added <code>.ws-team-skeleton[hidden] { display:
none; }</code>.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 7: Plugin Metadata Update</h3>
<p>The plugin author name was changed from Webskitters to <strong>Avijit
Dhar</strong>.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 8: Backend-Managed Bonus Features</h3>
<p>The AI audited all bonus requirements and added backend controls
for lazy loading, GSAP animation, skeleton loader, search filter,
department filter, ACF integration, and dark mode.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 9: Load More AJAX Refinement</h3>
<p>The load-more behavior was improved so it appends the next 8
members instead of replacing the grid with all visible members.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 10: Cards Per Row Control</h3>
<p>Because Elementor did not visibly show the first responsive
control, the AI moved row count settings into a separate backend
section named <code>Grid Settings</code>. It added desktop, tablet,
and mobile cards-per-row controls and render-time scoped CSS for
reliability.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 11: Image and Content Gap Fix</h3>
<p>The AI adjusted card image CSS so the image fills its wrapper
cleanly without unwanted spacing between the image and content area.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 12: Popup Trigger Update</h3>
<p>The user requested removal of the View Details button. The AI
updated the card markup and JavaScript so the popup opens when
clicking the image or team member title.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 13: Search Bar Enhancement</h3>
<p>The AI added a search icon inside the search field, a backend icon
picker, and a complete <code>Style &gt; Search Bar</code> panel for
width, colors, padding, border, radius, shadow, and icon size.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 14: Popup UI Fixes</h3>
<p>The AI aligned the popup close button properly, added spacing
above the popup CTA, and adjusted popup panel padding so content does
not overlap with the close button.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 15: Title Hover Removal</h3>
<p>After global button hover styles affected the clickable title, the
AI locked title button styles with scoped CSS so hover, focus, and
active states do not change color, background, underline, shadow, or
movement.</p>
<h3 class="western">Step 16: Button Editing Options</h3>
<p>The AI added Elementor-style button controls inside each team
member repeater item: button type, text, URL, icon, icon position,
icon spacing, and button ID. It updated frontend, AJAX, and popup
rendering to support these fields.</p>
